text: Angélica André (born 13 October 1994) is a Portuguese swimmer, specialising in open water events. She competed in the women's 10 km event at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships and she finished in 19th place. She also competed in the women's 25 km event, but did not finish the race. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Portuguese female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Female long- distance swimmers
